    <div class="body">
        <pre class="highlight"><code>
$db = Zend_Db::factory(
        'Mysqli',
        array(
            'host'     =&gt; 'xxx',
            'username' =&gt; 'xxx',
            'password' =&gt; 'xxx',
            'dbname'   =&gt; 'xxx'
        )
);
...

$query = "INSERT INTO foo VALUES('foo','bar')";
try {
    $db-&gt;query($query);
}
catch (Zend_Db_Exception $e) {
    if (!strstr($e-&gt;getMessage(), 'Duplicate')) {
        throw $e;
     }
}
</code></pre>

<p>The complete error message is:  Mysqli statement execute error : Duplicate entry '...' for key 1</p>

<p>As you can see I have to strstr() on the message to find the error, I think it would be a huge improvement if the exception returned a code as well - right now it returns "0", which is a bit too generic IMO. This is probably not the only case (query, adapter) where this happens.</p>

